BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:OGrmQAUWD9l5Fqmunv6bb
SUMMARY:Youth Clowning with Mick Holsbeke
DTSTAMP:20260406T013230Z
DTSTART:20260420T160000Z
DESCRIPTION:Unleash your silly side! A playful\\\, youth-friendly class usi
	ng improv\\\, physical comedy\\\, and clown games to build confidence & cr
	eativity\\n\\n\\n\\nGet ready to unleash your silly side! This series is a
	ll about having fun\\\, taking creative risks\\\, and finding the funny in
	 the unexpected. Working as a group to start\\\, participants will dive he
	ad-over-heels into ensemble theater\\\, improvisation\\\, physical comedy\
	\\, and clown-inspired games\\\, learning how to turn everyday moments int
	o laugh-out-loud comedy. Whether you’re interested in performing or just w
	ant to break out of your comfort zone\\\, this session is all about embrac
	ing play\\\, thinking on your feet\\\, and making bold comedic choices. No
	 experience? No problem! Just bring your imagination\\\, a sense of humor\
	\\, and a willingness to get ridiculous. \\nClass Details\\nDates: Six (6)
	 Monday classes \\nTime: 4:00 pm to 5:20 pm \\nLocation: The Clown Garage 
	at Improv School Eastside Issaquah \\n1315 NW Mall Street\\\, Suite 4 Issa
	quah\\\, WA 98027 (next to the Gaslamp Bar & Grill) \\nMaximum students: 1
	2 \\nAges: 10-15 \\nCost: $270 \\nPrerequisite: None\n\nhttps://www.unexpe
	ctedproductions.org/event/youth-clowning-with-mick-holsbeke/\n\nFrom Unexp
	ected Productions
URL:https://www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/youth-clowning-with-mick-ho
	lsbeke/
LOCATION:Clown Garage at the Improv School Issaquah\\\, 1315 NW Mall Street
	\\\, Suite 4\\\, Issaquah\\\, WA\\\, 98027
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:unexpected-productions
CATEGORIES:Unexpected Productions
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:jzAhPbCD-Zl_xh6GlFxE7
SUMMARY:Clown 100: The Foundations of Clown Play with Mick Holsbeke
DTSTAMP:20260406T013230Z
DTSTART:20260420T173000Z
DESCRIPTION:Step into the playful world of Clown! Explore presence\\\, vuln
	erability\\\, and joyful failure through ensemble play and laughter\\n\\n\
	\n\\nWelcome to the world of clowning! This foundational class invites you
	 to step into the playful\\\, unpredictable\\\, and joy-filled realm of Cl
	owning with other folks. Through a series of dynamic exercises in presence
	\\\, play\\\, rhythm\\\, tension\\\, emotional expression\\\, and ensemble
	 play\\\, participants will explore what makes Clown so hilarious and cont
	agious. Embracing vulnerability and the fine art of making mistakes\\\, we
	’ll turn failure into laughter and endless comic gold. Whether you’re new 
	to performance or a seasoned artist\\\, this series will help you build co
	nfidence\\\, take creative risks\\\, and refine your Clown instincts. Come
	 ready to play\\\, surprise yourself\\\, and find the fun in the unexpecte
	d! \\nClass Details\\nDates: Six (6) Mondays classes \\nTime: 7:00 pm to 8
	:30 pm \\nLocation: The Clown Garage at Improv School Eastside Issaquah \\
	n1315 NW Mall Street\\\, Suite 4 Issaquah\\\, WA 98027 (next to the Gaslam
	p Bar & Grill) \\nMaximum students: 16 \\nAges: 18 plus \\nCost: $270 \\nP
	rerequisite: None\n\nhttps://www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/clown-100
	-the-foundations-of-clown-play-with-mick-holsbeke-2/\n\nFrom Unexpected Pr
	oductions
URL:https://www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/clown-100-the-foundations-o
	f-clown-play-with-mick-holsbeke-2/
LOCATION:Unexpected Productions\\\, 1428 Post Alley at the Gum Wall in Pike
	 Place Market\\\, Seattle\\\, WA\\\, 98101\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:unexpected-productions
CATEGORIES:Unexpected Productions
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:Yy_cvAbiUfaFjoA5sVLTk
SUMMARY:NOCHE DE IMPROV EN ESPAÑOL
DTSTAMP:20260406T013230Z
DTSTART:20260420T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:Noche de Improvisación en español\\\, es una noche de jam para 
	los que hablan FLUIDAMENTE español\\\, que ya sean estudiantes actuales de
	 UP\\\, exalumnos de UP\\\, miembros del conjunto y exalumnos\\\, para jug
	ar juntos y seguir desarrollando sus habilidades de improvisación en españ
	ol. Noche de Improvisación en español \\\, está dirigida por Laila Valenci
	a. Los juegos ayudan a los improvisadores a desarrollar habilidades\\\, de
	sarrollar confianza y fomentar la creatividad. Pero lo mas importante es …
	 ¡es en español y es DIVERTIDO! El espacio es limitado a 16 personas. \\nF
	echa y hora: El tercer lunes de cada mes\\\, de 7 a 9 p. m. \\nUbicación: 
	650 S Orcas Suite 101\\\, Seattle\\\, WA 98108 \\nPrecio: $10 (11.24 con c
	argos) \\nEl Requisito Previo: Unexpected Productions Improv 100 \\nLaila 
	Valencia Nació en Guadalajara Jalisco México finales de los\\naños 70as\\\
	, donde vivió toda su infancia y adolescencia\\\, siempre tuvo interés por
	 las artes escénicas y participó en varios proyectos de teatro y danza con
	temporanea en la UDG \\\, a finales de los 90tas\\\, Se va a vivir a Seatt
	le WA donde conoce la técnica de comedia en improvisación \\\, de la cual 
	se enamora se inscribe en clases y talleres especializados\\\,con maestros
	 como Keith Johnstone creador de Theatresports\\\, Gorilla and Maestro imp
	rov shows\\\, Randy Dixon director artistico de Unexpected Produccions des
	de hace 20 anos\\\, talleres con Gary Austin\\\, Asiste a retiros de impro
	visacion en Nueva York con artistic new direcctins y desde entonces a part
	icipado en 6 festivales internacionales de improvisación\\\,A Impartido cl
	ases para toda las edades\\\, ahora es miembro de de la compañía más antig
	ua de improvisacionnen Seattle Unexpected Productions\\\, en la cual conti
	núa su preparación y actúa dos o mas veces por semana \\\, siempre está tr
	abajando en proyectos diferentes\\\, forma larga y corta de improv\\\, con
	tando historias que se inspiradan con las ideas del público.\n\nhttps://ww
	w.unexpectedproductions.org/event/noche-de-improv-en-espanol-2/2026-04-20/
	\n\nFrom Unexpected Productions
URL:https://www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/noche-de-improv-en-espanol-
	2/2026-04-20/
LOCATION:Unexpected Productions Improv School ISSAQUAH/EASTSIDE\\\, 1315 NW
	 Mall Street\\\, Suite 4\\\, Issaquah\\\, WA\\\, 98108\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:unexpected-productions
CATEGORIES:Unexpected Productions
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:d8ChIKx5qQSQfwqOMDrB6
SUMMARY:IMPROV 100 ISSAQUAH - Intro to Improv: Say Yes!\\\, SPRING '26
DTSTAMP:20260406T013230Z
DTSTART:20260420T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:Discover improv in Issaquah. Build confidence\\\, meet new peop
	le\\\, and learn to create stories through fun\\\, supportive games and sc
	ene work.\\n\\n\\n\\nLooking for a fun\\\, fresh way to connect with other
	s\\\, spark creativity\\\, and step out of the everyday routine? Welcome t
	o Intro to Improv at Unexpected Productions Improv School Eastside in Issa
	quah. Whether you are a working professional hoping to improve communicati
	on\\\, a creative soul searching for a new outlet\\\, or someone simply wa
	nting more laughter and community in your week\\\, this class is the perfe
	ct place to begin. \\nIn this beginner-friendly course\\\, you will learn 
	the foundational skills of improvisation: active listening\\\, collaborati
	on\\\, spontaneity\\\, and using your own life experiences to create hones
	t\\\, engaging scenes and stories. Improv is not about being funny\\\, it 
	is about being present\\\, supportive\\\, and open. And yes\\\, along the 
	way\\\, you will laugh more than you have in ages. \\nOur community values
	 connection and growth\\\, and this class is built on those principles. Yo
	u will work in a supportive group where the guiding philosophy is simple: 
	When your scene partner looks good\\\, you look good. Together\\\, we buil
	d trust\\\, confidence\\\, and creativity\\\, one scene at a time. \\n\\nU
	nder the guidance of our experienced faculty\\\, you will learn to:\\nBe a
	 better listener\\nConquer fears and build confidence\\nSpark creativity\\
	nMeet new people and make real connections\\nBecome a better problem solve
	r\\nSay yes more in your life\\nStep out of your comfort zone\\nImprove pu
	blic speaking\\nFail easier (and laugh about it)\\nDiscover more about you
	rself\\nHave an absolute blast\\n\\nThis class includes lots of laughter\\
	\, lots of stage time\\\, and zero pressure. Every student begins here. No
	 experience needed. Just bring curiosity and a willingness to try somethin
	g new. \\nUnexpected Productions Improv School is thrilled to bring our ne
	west Eastside improv classes to Issaquah\\\, serving the communities of th
	e Sammamish Plateau\\\, East Renton\\\, Bellevue\\\, Snoqualmie Valley\\\,
	 and beyond. \\nClass Details\\nDates: Six (8) Monday classes \\nTime: 7:0
	0pm to 9:00pm \\nLocation: Improv School Eastside Issaquah \\n1315 NW Mall
	 Street\\\, Suite 4 Issaquah\\\, WA 98027 (next to the Gaslamp Bar & Grill
	) \\nMaximum students: 16 \\nAges: 18 plus \\nCost: $320 \\nPrerequisite: 
	None \\nNote: Attendance at the first session is mandatory\\\, as it sets 
	the tone and foundation for the entire quarter. If you know you will miss 
	the first class\\\, please register for a future session.\n\nhttps://www.u
	nexpectedproductions.org/event/intro-to-improv-eastside-issaquah-mondays/\
	n\nFrom Unexpected Productions
URL:https://www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/intro-to-improv-eastside-is
	saquah-mondays/
LOCATION:Unexpected Productions Improv School ISSAQUAH/EASTSIDE\\\, 1315 NW
	 Mall Street\\\, Suite 4\\\, Issaquah\\\, WA\\\, 98108\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:unexpected-productions
CATEGORIES:Unexpected Productions
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:YdizphzBKkTYsK9LDo6Pc
SUMMARY:Improv Level Up: Turn Games into Scene Magic with Alan Hawkins - Is
	saquah
DTSTAMP:20260406T013230Z
DTSTART:20260421T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:Many improvisers begin with short-form games\\\, but hidden ins
	ide those fast\\\, playful formats are powerful tools for deeper scene wor
	k. In this four-week class\\\, we’ll explore how the instincts you already
	 use in games can strengthen your long-form improvisation. By unpacking th
	e mechanics behind classic games\\\, you’ll learn how to build stronger sc
	enes\\\, develop clearer relationships\\\, and create more confident impro
	vised storytelling. \\nThrough energetic exercises and supportive coaching
	\\\, you’ll discover how skills like listening\\\, commitment\\\, pattern 
	recognition\\\, and emotional connection can expand beyond the game struct
	ure and fuel longer\\\, richer scenes. If you’ve ever wondered how to brid
	ge the gap between short-form fun and long-form storytelling\\\, this clas
	s will help you make that leap. \\nClass Details\\nDates: Four (4) Tuesday
	s \\nTime: 7:00 pm–9:00 pm \\nLocation: Unexpected Productions – Issaquah 
	\\n1315 NW Mall Street\\\, Suite 4\\\, Issaquah\\\, WA 98027 (next to the 
	Gaslamp Bar and Grill) \\nMaximum Students: 16 \\nCost: $270 \\nPrerequisi
	te: Any Improv Class or Experience \\nMeet Your Instructor: Alan Hawkins\\
	nAlan Hawkins is an improviser from Los Angeles and Chicago with over two 
	decades of performance and teaching experience. A graduate of The Second C
	ity Conservatory\\\, The Second City Musical Conservatory\\\, iO West\\\, 
	Comedysportz Chicago\\\, and The Annoyance\\\, Alan has performed across t
	he U.S. and internationally with the acclaimed trio Extra Shelves and as a
	 guest with Grand Theft Improv in London. He has taught and directed for n
	umerous programs\\\, including the Teen Comedy Festival in Chicago. \\nAla
	n is an ensemble member of Unexpected Productions—America’s longest-runnin
	g Theatresports company—and the author of “YOU CAN’T LEARN IMPROV FROM A B
	OOK.” His classes are known for being energetic\\\, supportive\\\, and dee
	ply fun. \\nWhat to Bring\\nThis class involves movement\\\, so please dre
	ss comfortably and bring a bottle of water. \\nCancellation Policy\\nWe ar
	e unable to offer refunds.\n\nhttps://www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/
	theatrical-styles-with-alan-hawkins-issaquah-2/\n\nFrom Unexpected Product
	ions
URL:https://www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/theatrical-styles-with-alan
	-hawkins-issaquah-2/
LOCATION:Unexpected Productions Improv School ISSAQUAH/EASTSIDE\\\, 1315 NW
	 Mall Street\\\, Suite 4\\\, Issaquah\\\, WA\\\, 98108\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:unexpected-productions
CATEGORIES:Unexpected Productions
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:TSFRnm2vqYroCWhj2oHFz
SUMMARY:Improv Level Up: Turn Games into Scene Magic
DTSTAMP:20260406T013230Z
DTSTART:20260421T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:Many improvisers begin with short-form games\\\, but hidden ins
	ide those fast\\\, playful formats are powerful tools for deeper scene wor
	k. In this four-week class\\\, we’ll explore how the instincts you already
	 use in games can strengthen your long-form improvisation. By unpacking th
	e mechanics behind classic games\\\, you’ll learn how to build stronger sc
	enes\\\, develop clearer relationships\\\, and create more confident impro
	vised storytelling. \\nThrough energetic exercises and supportive coaching
	\\\, you’ll discover how skills like listening\\\, commitment\\\, pattern 
	recognition\\\, and emotional connection can expand beyond the game struct
	ure and fuel longer\\\, richer scenes. If you’ve ever wondered how to brid
	ge the gap between short-form fun and long-form storytelling\\\, this clas
	s will help you make that leap. \\nClass Details\\nDates: Four (4) Tuesday
	s \\nTime: 7:00 pm–9:00 pm \\nLocation: Unexpected Productions – Issaquah 
	\\n1315 NW Mall Street\\\, Suite 4\\\, Issaquah\\\, WA 98027 (next to the 
	Gaslamp Bar and Grill) \\nMaximum Students: 16 \\nCost: $270 \\nPrerequisi
	te: Any Improv Class or Experience \\nMeet Your Instructor: Alan Hawkins\\
	nAlan Hawkins is an improviser from Los Angeles and Chicago with over two 
	decades of performance and teaching experience. A graduate of The Second C
	ity Conservatory\\\, The Second City Musical Conservatory\\\, iO West\\\, 
	Comedysportz Chicago\\\, and The Annoyance\\\, Alan has performed across t
	he U.S. and internationally with the acclaimed trio Extra Shelves and as a
	 guest with Grand Theft Improv in London. He has taught and directed for n
	umerous programs\\\, including the Teen Comedy Festival in Chicago. \\nAla
	n is an ensemble member of Unexpected Productions—America’s longest-runnin
	g Theatresports company—and the author of “YOU CAN’T LEARN IMPROV FROM A B
	OOK.” His classes are known for being energetic\\\, supportive\\\, and dee
	ply fun. \\nWhat to Bring\\nThis class involves movement\\\, so please dre
	ss comfortably and bring a bottle of water. \\nCancellation Policy\\nWe ar
